description:
&lt;p&gt;Elm Tree Surgery is looking for a salaried GP to provide fixed-term maternity cover.   The role consists of 6 sessions - 2 sessions on each of Monday, Wednesday and Friday.  Our salaried GP is due to start her maternity leave at the beginning of February 2021 and we anticipate the role being approximately 10 months in duration.  For the right candidate this may lead to the offer of a permanent salaried GP position at the surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are a well-established single site dispensing practice serving a semi-rural population of approx 7,200 patients - our list is small enough to enable our GPs to provide continuity of care for their patients and whilst we are situated in a rural village the area has excellent links, both road and rail, to London, Oxford, Bristol and Bath. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are highly regarded by our patients and staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are regularly the top rated surgery in our area in the annual NHS GP patient survey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All our Partners and GPs have been registrars at the surgery and all agree that the work life balance at Elm Tree Surgery is excellent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have a low staff turnover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a training practice and our supportive team includes 4 Partners, 1 salaried GP, 3 practice nurses, 1 healthcare assistant/phlebotomist and excellent teams of receptionists and secretaries.  As part of one of four Primary Care Networks, under the umbrella of the Brunel Health Care Federation, we also benefit from First Contact Physiotherapists, Clinical Pharmacists, Pharmacy Technicians and a home visiting paramedic service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties of the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, reliable GP who is keen to be part of our committed and cohesive team. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will deal with a wide range of healthcare needs in a primary care setting, managing a caseload, ensuring the highest standards of care for all our patients and will be responsible for administration and paperwork arising directly from your caseload (referrals, investigations, results etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Duty doctor sessions will be in the same ratio as the Partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will attend our weekly Friday lunchtime multi-disciplinary team meetings – these are currently being held via Teams meetings and include GPs, PNs, community nurses, health visitors, community matrons, hospice out-reach team etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may have the opportunity to do extra locum sessions for the surgery on your non-working days and these will be remunerated separately.  If you wish to do locum sessions elsewhere or for other providers these must not be done on days when you are not scheduled to work one of your usual sessions at Elm Tree Surgery or on leave days without prior written agreement from the Partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TPP, SystmOne, Ardens, accuRx&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competive salary based on experience and skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold the appropriate medical qualifications required in order to practice medicine in the UK &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be included as a fully registered doctor in the GP Register of the General Medical Council. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be included on the Medical Performers’ List.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not be suspended or disqualified from practice under any disciplinary proceedings that may result in any such disqualification or censure on the grounds of professional misconduct or negligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elm Tree Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High Street&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shrivenham&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swindon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SN6 8AG&lt;/p&gt;
